  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 2 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 high, 3 medium, 30 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI); plus 3 other bases. 3 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and RVR limitations  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF). Primary drivers: low cloud base, low‑visibility procedures and low‑visibility takeoff restrictions. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Billund (BLL/EKBI), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA) and 9 others.",
